 <body>
   <div class="container">
     <h1>I love MATCHA</h1>
 
     <p>
       My name is Mauricio Moreno-Jones and I am the developer of this website.
       I just want everyone to know that I love MATCHA!
     </p>
 
     <p id="question">Do you like MATCHA?</p>
     <button onclick="handleAnswer('yes')">Yes</button>
     <button onclick="handleAnswer('no')">No</button>
     <div id="response"></div>
   </div>
 
   <!-- Scrollable Paragraph -->
   <div class="scrollable-paragraph">
     <p>Here's a simple recipe for a delicious iced matcha latte:</p>
 
     <p>Ingredients:</p>
     <ul>
       <li>1-2 tsp matcha powder (depending on how strong you like it)</li>
       <li>2 oz hot water (not boiling, around 175°F or 80°C)</li>
       <li>1-2 tsp sweetener (like honey, sugar, or agave), optional</li>
       <li>1/2 cup milk or milk alternative (like almond, oat, or soy milk)</li>
       <li>Ice cubes</li>
     </ul>
 
     <p>Instructions:</p>
     <ol>
       <li><strong>Prepare the Matcha:</strong><br>
           Sift the matcha powder into a small bowl to avoid clumps. Pour the hot water over the matcha powder. Whisk the matcha and water together using a matcha whisk (or a regular whisk) in a zigzag motion until it’s fully dissolved and frothy.</li>
 
       <li><strong>Sweeten (Optional):</strong><br>
           If you like a sweeter latte, stir in your choice of sweetener while the matcha is still warm so it dissolves easily.</li>
 
       <li><strong>Assemble the Latte:</strong><br>
           Fill a glass with ice cubes. Pour the prepared matcha over the ice.</li>
 
       <li><strong>Add Milk:</strong><br>
           Pour your milk or milk alternative into the glass. Adjust the amount to your liking based on how creamy or strong you want your latte.</li>
 
       <li><strong>Stir & Enjoy:</strong><br>
           Stir the matcha and milk together until well combined. Enjoy your refreshing iced matcha latte!</li>
     </ol>
 
     <p>You can also adjust the sweetness and milk ratio depending on your taste. Enjoy!</p>
   </div>
 
   <script>
     function handleAnswer(answer) {
       const responseDiv = document.getElementById('response');
       const heading = document.querySelector('h1');
       const paragraph = document.querySelector('p');
       const buttons = document.querySelectorAll('button');
       const question = document.getElementById('question');
 
       // Hide all content except for the response (but keep the recipe visible)
       heading.style.display = 'none';
       paragraph.style.display = 'none';
       buttons.forEach(button => button.style.display = 'none');
       question.style.display = 'none'; // Hide the question after the button is pressed
 
       // Display the output based on user input, convert it to lowercase and add an exclamation mark
       if (answer === 'yes') {
         responseDiv.textContent = 'fantastic!'.toLowerCase();  // Output in lowercase with exclamation mark
       } else if (answer === 'no') {
         responseDiv.textContent = 'you stink!'.toLowerCase();  // Output in lowercase with exclamation mark
       }
     }
   </script>
